text.section:
An entity name may not contain language stating or implying that the entity is organized for a purpose other than that allowed by the entity's:
Articles of incorporation, if the entity is a corporation;
Articles of organization, if the entity is a limited liability company;
Certificate of limited liability partnership, if the entity is a limited liability partnership;
Certificate of limited partnership, if the entity is a limited partnership; or
Articles of incorporation, if the entity is a professional corporation.
